review_data: Reviewed in the United States on November 22, 2020
name: wildflower
title: Absolutely respect this dairy
review: We buy organic dairy. Advantages with their yogurt: best tasting we have ever tried (having eaten yogurt over many years and many brands). Milk: excellent. Best of all: the origin of their products is one dairy. Not any slew of dairies. To add to the benefits, they are a coop and support environmentalism. They welcome visits and keep up with their customers via email in a welcoming, helpful way. The only sad part: they're trying to compete with trends. Nevertheless they remain solid with real food.

title: Tastes BETTER then Whole Milk and has fraction of callories.
review: For years I was avoiding this thinking that no fat will result in some inferior flavor.Last time I have been shopping the whole milk one was out of stock so Igot this one instead.I was so pleasantly impressed with the flavor that is just divine. So fully bodied texture,so filling and satisfyingly and without all the calories.I was truly happy with the purchase and I am going to switch to it from now on.I don't need extra calories from fat as I get my fat from other sources in sufficientamount.Taste: Fabulous!Do I Recommend: YES!
